Capabilites of the video encoder/decoder.

Field Documentation

UINT32 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_application_categories
 

All the supported application categories flag bits will be set (see CodecDevice::ApplicationCategoriesFlagsType), e.g. if the codec supports both Storage & Streaming then it will be set to "3".

CodecType* CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_array_of_supported_codecs
 

Array of the supported video codecs. The number of elements is given by m_num_of_supported_codecs.

UINT32 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_max_bit_rate
 

Maximum supported bit rate (in bits per second).

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_max_frame_rate_denominator
 

Denominator of the maximum supported frame rate (in frames per second). The actual maximum frame rate is calculated as m_max_frame_rate_numerator/m_max_frame_rate_denominator.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_max_frame_rate_numerator
 

Numerator of the maximum supported frame rate (in frames per second). The actual maximum frame rate is calculated as m_max_frame_rate_numerator/m_max_frame_rate_denominator.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_max_height
 

Maximum supported height.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_max_quality_level
 

Maximum supported quality level. In case of Video Decoder this will indicate the Deinterlacing, Deringing & Deblocking capabilities

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_max_width
 

Maximum supported width.

UINT32 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_min_bit_rate
 

Minimum supported bit rate (in bits per second).

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_min_frame_rate_denominator
 

Denominator of the minimum supported frame rate (in frames per second). The actual minimum frame rate is calculated as m_min_frame_rate_numerator/m_min_frame_rate_denominator.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_min_frame_rate_numerator
 

Numerator of the minimum supported frame rate (in frames per second). The actual minimum frame rate is calculated as m_min_frame_rate_numerator/m_min_frame_rate_denominator.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_min_height
 

Minimum supported height.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_min_quality_level
 

Minimum supported quality level. In case of Video Decoder this will indicate the Deinterlacing, Deringing & Deblocking capabilities. 0 corresponds to default settings.

UINT16 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_min_width
 

Minimum supported width.

UINT8 CodecDevice::VideoCodecCapabilities::m_num_of_supported_codecs
 

Number of supported video codecs. It is also the length (number of elements) of m_array_of_supported_codecs.
